  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.8.0-unstable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux OpenWrt (800MHz CPU 64MB RAM 1GB SWAP)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nUnlocking JSON keystore file (created by Geth binary)  takes 1-2 seconds\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nUnlocking encrypted JSON file, created by Geth, takes 10-15 minutes\r\n\r\nHowever; Using keys created by MyEtherWallet takes the normal 1-2 second unlock time. I am having to convert my keys to the format MyEtherWallet uses. In my embedded environment, the Geth binary prefers the keystore JSON format of MyEtherWallet, not the default that Geth executable creates.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nUsing \"geth account new\" also is also taking longer than usual. Must have a low RAM environment\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
